OL,3,CIs turkey losing its place as the
OL,4,Ccentrepiece of the UK Christmas dinner
OL,5,Ctable?
OL,7,FThe turkey has long been a Christmas
OL,8,Fdinner staple, but new figures suggest
OL,9,Fit could be falling out of favour, as
OL,10,Fother meats take a bite of its crown.
OL,12,FJust over half of UK households (52%)
OL,13,Fwill have turkey for their main meal
OL,14,Fthis Christmas, down from 60% in 2019,
OL,15,Fthe grocery insight charity IGD has
OL,16,Ffound.
OL,18,FA quarter of people are opting for
OL,19,Fchicken on their plates instead,
OL,20,Fcompared to just 16% six years ago.
