OL,3,CIs turkey losing its place as the
OL,4,Ccentrepiece of the UK Christmas dinner
OL,5,Ctable?
OL,7,FThe turkey's path to popularity was a
OL,8,Fgradual one - taking over from the
OL,9,Fgoose in the 1950s as the default meat
OL,10,Fon Christmas tables.
OL,12,FTurkeys were first brought to Europe
OL,13,Ffrom North America in the sixteenth
OL,14,Fcentury. Henry VIII is thought to be
OL,15,Fthe first monarch to feast on turkey
OL,16,Fat Christmas, though it wasn't until
OL,17,Fthe reign of Queen Victoria that
OL,18,Fturkeys were widely eaten as a festive
OL,19,Fcentrepiece.
